# ATL311 Civic Intake Platform — Cursor Rules

## Tech Stack
- Framework: Next.js 14 App Router (TypeScript)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS
- ORM: Prisma v7 with PrismaPg driver adapter
- Database: PostgreSQL via Supabase
- AI: Anthropic Claude API (claude-sonnet-4-6)
- Auth: NextAuth.js
- Email: Resend
- Testing: Jest (unit), Supertest (integration), Playwright (E2E)

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode — never use 'any'
- Functional components only — no class components
- Async/await only — never callbacks or .then() chains
- Named exports for components, default exports for pages
- Error handling: try/catch on every async function, log with context
- Database: always use DIRECT_URL (:5432) for migrations, never pooler (:6543)
- Imports: use @/ alias for all internal imports
- No magic numbers — extract to named constants

## Testing (MANDATORY)
- Unit tests: every API route, every helper function
- Integration tests: form submit → Claude → database → dashboard
- E2E tests: Playwright — resident submits, operator approves
- Coverage threshold: 80% minimum — CI fails below this
- Never ship untested code to production

## Logging
- Audit logs: store in database (immutable) — routing decisions, status changes, operator actions
- Debug logs: Vercel logs only — Claude API calls, DB queries, errors
- NEVER log: full resident description, raw Claude API response (PII)
- Track Claude routing accuracy: log every decision + operator override for drift detection

## Security
- Never commit API keys — all secrets in .env.local
- Rate limit all API endpoints
- CAPTCHA on resident submission form
- Sanitize all form inputs before storing
- WCAG 2.1 AA compliance: semantic HTML, ARIA labels, keyboard navigation, color contrast 4.5:1
- Data residency: US-East region only

## Database
- Migrations: DIRECT_URL (:5432) only, never pooler
- Routing and StatusHistory tables are IMMUTABLE — never update, only insert
- Always add indexes on foreign keys and frequently queried fields
- Use SELECT FOR UPDATE on capacity checks to prevent race conditions
